def transform(sequence):
    sequence = list(sequence)
    for i in range(len(sequence) - 1):
        if sequence[i].isnumeric() and sequence[i+1] == '0':
            for j in range(i+1, len(sequence)):
                if sequence[j] != '0':
                    break
                sequence[j] = sequence[i]
    return "".join(sequence)
```
Please note that the input to the function should be a string. This function works by iterating the sequence from the first (0th) index to the 2nd last index. When it finds a non-zero character followed by a '0', it changes all the '0' characters from the next position to the desired number until it encounters a non-zero character. This way, it transforms each sequence to the desired sequence.
